# DAX Measures Reference

All measures are stored in the `_Measures` table in the Power BI semantic model.

---

## Total Sales
```dax
Total Sales = SUM(gold_daily_sales[sales])
```
**Purpose:** Base measure. Sums all sales in the current filter context.
All time intelligence measures depend on this.

---

## Sales LY
```dax
Sales LY = CALCULATE([Total Sales], SAMEPERIODLASTYEAR(DateTable[Date]))
```
**Purpose:** Total Sales shifted back exactly one year.
Requires DateTable marked as date table with active relationship to gold_daily_sales.

---

## YoY Growth %
```dax
YoY Growth % = DIVIDE([Total Sales] - [Sales LY], [Sales LY])
```
**Purpose:** Year-over-year growth rate as a percentage.
DIVIDE used instead of / to handle blank denominator gracefully for 2013 dates.

---

## Avg Daily Sales
```dax
Avg Daily Sales = AVERAGEX(VALUES(DateTable[Date]), [Total Sales])
```
**Purpose:** Average daily sales total across the current filter period.
AVERAGEX iterates at the day level to avoid averaging at store/product grain.

---

## Sales on Promo
```dax
Sales on Promo = CALCULATE([Total Sales], gold_daily_sales[onpromotion] = 1)
```
**Purpose:** Total Sales filtered to promotion days only.
Uses = 1 instead of = TRUE because onpromotion is stored as BIT type from Fabric.

---

## Promo Uplift %
```dax
Promo Uplift % = DIVIDE([Sales on Promo], [Total Sales] - [Sales on Promo]) - 1
```
**Purpose:** Ratio of promotion sales vs non-promotion sales.
Positive value means promotions are driving incremental sales above baseline.

---

## Holiday Sales
```dax
Holiday Sales = CALCULATE([Total Sales], gold_daily_sales[is_holiday] = 1)
```
**Purpose:** Total Sales on national holiday dates only.
is_holiday flag built in Silver layer and carried through gold_daily_sales view.

---

## High Risk Stores
```dax
High Risk Stores = 
COUNTROWS(
    FILTER(
        gold_inventory_risk, 
        gold_inventory_risk[reorder_risk_level] = "HIGH RISK"
    )
)
```
**Purpose:** Count of store and product family combinations at HIGH RISK
reorder level. Driven by weekly demand forecast threshold in gold_inventory_risk view.

---

## Weeks of Supply
```dax
Weeks of Supply = DIVIDE(SUM(gold_daily_sales[sales]), [Avg Daily Sales] * 7)
```
**Purpose:** Weeks of demand represented by current sales volume.
Note: uses sales as proxy for on-hand stock. In production this would use
actual stock figures from ERP system.

---

## Rolling 7D Sales
```dax
Rolling 7D Sales = 
CALCULATE(
    [Total Sales], 
    DATESINPERIOD(
        DateTable[Date], 
        LASTDATE(DateTable[Date]), 
        -7, 
        DAY
    )
)
```
**Purpose:** Total Sales for the 7-day window ending on the last visible date.
Used as a smoothed trend line in time series visuals to reduce daily noise.